							<div class="post">Firstly, = is assignment, == is comparison, so this:<br /><div class="codeheader">Code:</div><div class="code">&nbsp; if(buttonState1 = 1 &amp;&amp; limitsw.uniquePress())<br /></div>should be<br /><div class="codeheader">Code:</div><div class="code"> <br />if(buttonState1 == 1 &amp;&amp; limitsw.uniquePress())<br /></div>However, note also, that you never reset buttonState1 (or 2 for that matter), so once you&#039;ve pressed the button, it&#039;s stepping action will be invoked on every iteration of loop - you need an else on the checking ifs that puts it back to 0.</div>
